Fig. 10. (A) Bright-field image of 0.5 mm glass beads glued together by a worm in a lab aquarium. (B) SEM image of an adhesive joint between glass beads. (C) SEM image of glue fractured after lyophilization. (D) Optical section of unfixed and hydrated glue using intrinsic fluorescence. (E) SEM image of fixed and sectioned glue. (F) Super-resolution fluorescence micrograph of fixed and sectioned glue using an anti-pS antibody.
